cs.DC, cs.NA, cs.MS, cs.SE, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the parallelization of numerical linear algebra algorithms on multicore architectures, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper deals with the computation of the inverse of a symmetric positive definite matrix, which is a topic within numerical analysis. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses the implementation of numerical linear algebra algorithms using existing software libraries (e.g. LAPACK) and the use of compiler techniques to optimize performance, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the translation of existing LAPACK code to a tile algorithm and the use of compiler techniques to optimize performance, which are topics within software engineering. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper focuses on improving the parallelism and performance of numerical linear algebra algorithms on multicore architectures, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
